Installation and configuration of Virtual Environment and Flask library

1) create a folder called flasktutorial
2) open the folder flasktutorial inside the visula studio code
3) go to terminal and run the command "python -m venv virtual"
4) you can see the virtual folder is created
5) to activate the virtual environment "cd virtual\scripts"
6) type "activate"
7) you can see (virtual) current working folder path
8) let us install flask libraries inside the virtual environmne
9) type cd...and again cd..
10) now you will be inside the flasktutorial
11) now you type pip install flask
12) the prev command will install all the necessary library inside the virtual\Lib\site-packages folder
13) to come out of virtual of environment
14) type cd virtual
15) type cd Scripts
16) type cd activate/ deactivate

Developing web application using flask


1) cretae a python program called app.python 
2) in the terminal mkae sure yiu are inside the folder where the app.py is